HEADWORD: Proruption
<hw>Pro*rup"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proruptio</ets>, fr. <ets>prorumpere</ets>, <ets>proruptum</ets>,
to break forth; <ets>pro</ets> forth + <ets>rumpere</ets> to
break.]</ety> <def>The act or state of bursting forth; a bursting
out.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
